Vizualtions of Part I: Understanding the problems(The Big Picture)

Plot 1

visualize(
  loanData, 
  xvar = "year", 
  yvar = "loan_amnt", 
  type = "line", 
  linecol = "blue", 
  pointcol = "blue", 
  fun = "sum", 
  theme = "theme_bw", 
  labs = list(
    title = "Total Loan Amount trend over the years", 
    x = "Year", y = "Total Loan Amount"
  ), 
  custom = FALSE
)

Plot 4 Rate of Default over the years

result <- pivotr(
  loanData, 
  cvars = "year", 
  nvar = "label", 
  fun = "sum", 
  normalize = "total", 
  data_filter = "label ==1", 
  tabsort = "year", 
  nr = Inf
)
summary(result, perc = TRUE)
Pivot table
Data        : loanData 
Filter      : label ==1 
Table sorted: year 
Categorical : year 
Normalize by: total 
Numeric     : label 
Function    : sum

  2012   1.453%
  2013   7.540%

Plot 5 Number of Charged Off customers with respect to Grades

visualize(
  loanData, 
  xvar = "grade", 
  type = "dist", 
  fill = "grade", 
  linecol = "blue", 
  theme = "theme_bw", 
  data_filter = "label ==1", 
  custom = FALSE
)
